  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosed Inflammatory Bowel Disease

          -  Colectomy with Jpouch or ileostomy

          -  Ileostomy alone with less than 30 cm of small bowel resected

          -  A diverting ileostomy is permitted

          -  Jpouch alone

          -  Stable disease activity with no or mild inflammation felt not to significantly impact
             gastrointestinal (GI) output.

          -  Any of the following:

          -  Need for IV fluids &gt;2x/month

          -  Intake of &gt; 1.5 liters of oral fluid daily

          -  GI output of &gt; 1.5 liters in a 24 hour period for three days during a 14 day period
             (does not need to be consecutive days)

          -  Stable doses of anti-diarrheal agents, octreotide or Gattex

          -  Stable doses of anti-inflammatory agents and/or antibiotics

          -  Willing to comply with study visits and assessments

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Chronic renal insufficiency glomerular filtration rate (GFR) &lt; 40

          -  Significant chronic liver disease altering fluid balance

          -  Uncontrolled flare of inflammatory disease

          -  An anticipated change in medication in the next 3 months

          -  Anticipated gastrointestinal surgery in the subsequent 3 months

          -  Diabetes

          -  Use of Lactulose/Mannitol solution is contraindicated
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
